In this press briefing, Press Secretary Jay Carney addresses questions about the White House's knowledge of the IRS scandal. Carney explains that the White House Counsel was notified of the Inspector General's audit on April 24th, but she did not inform the President because it was an ongoing investigation and there was no need for the President to intervene. Carney emphasizes that there was no interference from the White House in the investigation and that the President took action as soon as the report was published. Carney also discusses the President's views on press freedoms and the need to balance national security interests with the First Amendment. He defends the President's support for the media shield law and emphasizes the importance of protecting classified information. Carney also addresses questions about the situation in Iraq and the U.S. government's engagement with Myanmar.